  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f4d28b56-1c92-4c4d-9b3e-7a5e2c1f2014",
    "name": "Hiveboard Task 14 - Notification Engine Verification",
    "description": "Postman collection for manually verifying Task 14 acceptance criteria from IMPLEMENTATION-GUIDE.md.\n\nRecommended setup:\n1. Start the API in Development mode so EF Core migrations run automatically.\n2. Set HIVEBOARD_ADMIN_KEY before starting the API so it matches the adminApiKey collection variable.\n3. Run the requests top-to-bottom in a single Runner pass; the collection registers its own worker agents and seeds an isolated project, two tasks (A and B), and one decomposition target (C) per run.\n\nValidates the five acceptance criteria:\n- AC1 — agents can poll /api/v1/agents/me/notifications for unacknowledged notifications.\n- AC2 — agents can acknowledge notifications via /api/v1/agents/me/notifications/{id}/ack.\n- AC3 — TaskAssigned, TaskBlocked, ReviewRequested, TaskDecomposed, and DependencyResolved all fire correctly.\n- AC4 — notifications are agent-scoped (Worker-1 and Worker-2 inboxes are disjoint).\n- AC5 — acknowledging another agent's notification returns 404 and does not mutate state.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
